			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I am just curious what augmentations other mages are putting into the type one and two slots for Immortal's Bloodied silk.  I suspect it depends a lot on that person's current gear, their goals, and what they tend to fight.
<br />

<br />
Personally I'm not interested in INT augs since I can still buy ten levels of advanced innate INT (AA count isn't a concern till another expansion) and STA augs are only mildly interesting since boar is getting me close to the cap.  I think that leaves resists, HP, and mana augments.  My resists are decent (all 150-190ish), so I think maybe HP or mana would be a better route to go.  I was disappointed to see the 20 HP/mana aug can't be put in Immortal's Bloodied armor.  Any mages out there with similar gear care to comment on how they view augmentations?
<br />

<br />
If it matters, what I tend to fight in groups are normal LDoN missions (occasionally hards) and some of the exp spots (BoT, HoH, PoV, CoD, Tactics) if some friends drag me to have some fun with them.  Raids are smallish with targets like BoT towers, Xanamech, Korucust, and maybe some Luclin/Velious targets if I can twist enough arms to get them to try stuff for a first time.<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=108671" target="_blank" class="postlink">Varia Darselai</a> Arch Convoker</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
